969438124968460552%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Y%20Combinator%20President%20and%20CEO%20Garry%20Tan%20on%20X%20on%20Saturday.%20Early-stage%20teams%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20simply%20can't%20swallow%20a%20tax%20that%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20accompanied%20by%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%2C%20speaks%20after%20signing%20an%20executive%20order%20imposing%20a%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20on%20H1B%20visas%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20at%20the%20White%20House.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68d0696d57d362d375e894ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20accompanied%20by%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%2C%20speaks%20after%20signing%20an%20executive%20order%20imposing%20a%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20on%20H1B%20visas%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harnik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESophie%20Alcorn%2C%20founder%20of%20Alcorn%20Law%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20California%2C%20whose%20clients%20include%20venture%20capital%20firms%20and%20small%20startups%2C%20said%20smaller%20companies%20and%20startups%20could%20be%20hit%20hard%20by%20the%20change%20if%20they%20find%20the%20%24100%2C000%20tab%20prohibitive.%20By%20comparison%2C%20she%20said%2C%20Big%20Tech%20could%20absorb%20the%20cost%20for%20some%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMenlo%20Ventures'%20Das%20said%20the%20math%20alone%20shows%20why%20startups%20are%20most%20exposed.%20%26quot%3BAn%20early-stage%20startup%20is%20probably%20not%20paying%20too%20much%20more%20than%20like%20%24150%2C000%20to%20%24200%2C000%20for%20base%20salaries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you're%20looking%20at%20%24150%2C000%20to%20%24200%2C000%20and%20you%20say%2C%20hey%2C%20let's%20tack%20on%20a%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20makes%20it%20a%20little%20bit%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20hire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Hornik%2C%20a%20founding%20partner%20at%20Lobby%20Capital%2C%20said%20the%20consequences%20go%20beyond%20balance%20sheets.%20%26quot%3BAny%20impediment%20to%20H-1B%20visas%20is%20a%20detriment%20to%20the%20country%20and%20startups%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20startup%20world%20relies%20heavily%20on%20the%20expertise%20of%20foreign%20citizens.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20going%20to%20create%20an%20impediment%20to%20hiring%20the%20best%20possible%20people%2C%20then%20we%20will%20be%20creating%20an%20impediment%20to%20creating%20the%20best%20possible%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHornik%20said%20hiring%20Americans%20has%20never%20been%20the%20issue.%20Startups%20want%20the%20best%20candidates%20wherever%20they%20are.%20If%20US%20immigration%20rules%20make%20it%20too%20difficult%20to%20bring%20those%20workers%20here%2C%20he%20said%2C%20young%20companies%20will%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20spread%20their%20teams%20across%20borders%20and%20hire%20talent%20abroad%20instead%20of%20building%20in%20America%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22317554b2-9979-484d-99cf-09226344366f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BThey'll%20just%20move%20the%20jobs%20to%20Vancouver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20isn't%20just%20about%20cost.%20It%20risks%20pushing%20jobs%20out%20of%20the%20US%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Rahbar%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20founded%20the%20boutique%20firm%20the%20Rahbar%20Group%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20even%20among%20the%20tech%20heavyweights%2C%20the%20cost%20would%20likely%20dissuade%20some%20hiring.%20He%20said%20that%20if%20it%20remains%20in%20place%2C%20big%20companies%20could%20shift%20work%20overseas%20to%20where%20the%20talent%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20executive%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20company%20could%20simply%20shift%20more%20workers%20to%20Canada%2C%20where%20immigration%20laws%20are%20friendlier.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20US%20doesn't%20get%20%24100%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20probably%20loses%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20federal%20and%20state%20tax%20revenue%20per%20immigrant.%20No%20net%20new%20US%20jobs%20will%20be%20created.%20They'll%20just%20move%20the%20jobs%20to%20Vancouver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Google%20manager%20remarked%20that%20the%20company%20had%20been%20offshoring%20many%20roles%20in%20some%20of%20its%20units%2C%20instead%20hiring%20in%20locations%20such%20as%20Mexico%20and%20India%2C%20and%20that%20they%20expected%20the%20executive%20order%20would%20only%20accelerate%20that.%20Another%20Google%20employee%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFor%20a%20company%20as%20big%20as%20ours%2C%20I%20can%20just%20see%20us%20hiring%20more%20abroad%20instead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20American%20tech%20companies%20have%20already%20been%20expanding%20outside%20traditional%20hubs%20like%20the%20Bay%20Area%20and%20New%20York%2C%20and%20setting%20up%20offices%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20Mexico%20City%2C%20and%20Bangalore.%20This%20order%2C%20insiders%20say%2C%20only%20gives%20them%20more%20reason%20to%20accelerate%20those%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDas%20agrees%20that%20the%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20will%20continue%20to%20grow%20offices%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20additional%20incentive%20for%20them%20to%20continue%20to%20accelerate%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Finkelman%2C%20an%20immigration%20attorney%20from%20Austin%20who%20has%20been%20advising%20companies%20on%20employment-based%20immigration%20for%20more%20than%2015%20years%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20order%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20be%20tested%20in%20court.%20While%20presidents%20have%20broad%20leeway%20to%20issue%20executive%20orders%2C%20he%20said%2