ven%20though%20I%20had%20a%20master's%2C%20the%20odds%20were%20still%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20playing%20the%20slots%20at%20Las%20Vegas.%20You%20win%20a%20few%20times%2C%20but%20you%20lose%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20control%20over%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20first%20H-1B%20miss%2C%20I%20started%20looking%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-einstein-o1-visa-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EO-1%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20heard%20about%20from%20my%20colleagues.%20The%20O-1%20visa%20is%20reserved%20for%20individuals%20with%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%26quot%3B%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20eight%20categories%20for%20eligibility%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20satisfy%20at%20least%20three%20of%20them.%20When%20I%20went%20through%20it%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20already%20satisfied%20at%20least%20two%20of%20the%20criteria%3A%20I%20had%20published%20work%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20I%20used%20to%20judge%20hackathons%2C%20and%20I%20used%20to%20review%20papers%20for%20other%20conference%20journals.%20I%20had%20about%20six%20years%20of%20contributions%20to%20my%20field%20in%20AI%20under%20my%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20things%20I%20was%20already%20doing%2C%20but%20they%20lined%20up%20well%20with%20the%20O-1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250f71783-82bf-4690-a3db-8e09219a3750%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStaying%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20originally%20from%20Bangalore%2C%20India.%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-stock-picks-bargain-prices-tariffs-market-crash-trump-recession-2025-4%23kimberly-clark-corporation-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKimberly-Clark%20Corporation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebefore%20I%20came%20to%20the%20US%20to%20pursue%20my%20master's%20degree%20in%20information%20systems%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20come%20for%20a%20master's%2C%20you're%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fforeign-students-us-visa-social-media-account-public-state-department-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EF-1%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20US%20through%20an%20OPT%2C%20or%20optional%20practical%20training%2C%20which%20granted%20me%20temporary%20work%20authorization%20in%20the%20US%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20three%20years%20were%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaily-life-ibm-head-vc-emily-fontaine-starups-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eat%20IBM%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20lined%20up%20with%20my%20three%20H-1B%20chances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMissing%20out%20on%20an%20H-1B%20was%20definitely%20disappointing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20just%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20having%20a%20bad%20day%20at%20the%20casino%2C%20not%20winning%20anything.%20However%2C%20the%20feeling%20of%20disappointment%20was%20amplified%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20let%20it%20get%20to%20me.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20learning%20and%20contributing%20a%20lot%20here.%20That's%20why%20the%20O-1%20visa%20seemed%20like%20a%20very%20good%20option%20for%20people%20who%20want%20to%20contribute%20long-term%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249190daa-4077-43d7-b854-ab1e22892c2f%5C%22%3EGetting%20the%20O-1%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20doing%20work%20solely%20for%20a%20visa.%20My%20focus%20has%20always%20been%20on%20my%20field%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-cofounder-anthropic-mike-krieger-how-software-engineering-work-changing-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20and%20software%20engineering%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20way%2C%20I've%20worked%20on%20research%20papers%2C%20contributed%20to%20open-source%20projects%2C%20reviewed%20papers%2C%20and%20judged%20hackathons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20things%20I%20was%20already%20doing%2C%20but%20they%20lined%20up%20well%20with%20the%20O-1%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20the%20O-1%20visa%20late%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20go%20to%20the%20website%20where%20I%20could%20track%20the%20status%20of%20the%20application%20every%20night.%20I%20kept%20reading%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20%26quot%3BProcessing.%20Processing.%20Processing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20when%20that%20would%20change.%20All%20I%20knew%20was%20that%20it%20would%20happen%20within%2015%20business%20days%20since%20I%20applied%20for%20the%20premium%20processing%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%2012th%20business%20day%2C%20I%20opened%20my%20laptop%20around%205%3A30%20p.m.%20I%20clicked%20on%20the%20status%20and%20saw%20it%20magically%20changed.%20My%20application%20was%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20a%20bit%20of%20mixed%20emotions.%20I%20was%20so%20relieved%20that%20I%20was%20finally%20approved.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20hard%20work%2C%20but%20it%20felt%20nice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20I%20said%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20playing%20slots%20in%20Vegas.%20Only%20this%20time%20I%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cb5fe40-26a3-461d-8b9d-c6064c0b73b1%5C%22%3EAdvice%20to%20other%20O-1%20seekers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20O-1%20visa%20is%20called%20the%20Einstein%20visa%20for%20a%20reason.%20It%20takes%20time%20and%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20it%20took%20six%20years%20of%20work%20%E2%80%94%20from%20my%20time%20at%20Kimberly-Clark%2C%20to%20my%20master's%20degree%2C%20and%20then%20my%20job%20at%20IBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20focused%20on%20your%20field%20and%20passionate%20about%20it%2C%20you'll%20naturally%20start%20to%20meet%20the%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetworking%20is%20also%20important.%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20known%20about%20the%20O-1%