butions%20of%20major%20significance%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEvidence%20of%20the%20applicant's%20authorship%20of%20scholarly%20articles%2C%20professional%20journals%2C%20or%20other%20major%20media%20in%20the%20field%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEvidence%20that%20the%20applicant%20has%20worked%20in%20a%20critical%20role%20or%20essential%20capacity%20for%20employers%20that%20have%20a%20distinguished%20reputation%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEvidence%20that%20the%20applicant%20has%20either%20commanded%20a%20high%20salary%20or%20will%20command%20a%20high%20salary%20in%20their%20work%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20eligible%2C%20an%20applicant%20must%20meet%20at%20least%20three%20of%20the%20criteria%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0though%20more%20make%20for%20a%20stronger%20application%2C%20Logan%20Ullyott%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Ullyott%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigration-firm-helping-ai-engineers-qualify-for-h-b-alternative-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EO-1%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%20holder%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Compass%20Visas%2C%20a%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20visa%20and%20green%20card%20support%20for%20people%20in%20business%20and%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20O-1%20is%20an%20occupation-agnostic%20visa%2C%26quot%3B%20Ullyott%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20get%20an%20O-1%20if%20you're%20an%20engineer%20or%20a%20researcher%2C%20you%20can%20also%20get%20it%20if%20you're%20an%20influencer%2C%20a%20cook%2C%C2%A0or%20really%20any%20occupation.%20So%20it's%20a%20more%20wide-open%20visa%20category%2C%20and%20it's%20intended%20to%20go%20to%20people%20who%20can%20demonstrate%20that%20they%20are%20at%20the%20top%20of%20their%20field.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acee08f2-90dd-498b-9b84-67aa3b611866%5C%22%3EA%20specialized%20alternative%20to%20the%20H-1B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETanush%20Sharanarthi%2C%20an%20IBM%20software%20engineer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20failed%20to%20get%20an%20H-1B%20visa%20three%20times%20before%20applying%20for%20an%20O-1%20visa%20this%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESharanarthi%20said%20he%20landed%20the%20O-1%20visa%20by%20highlighting%20six%20years%20of%20work%20in%20his%20field%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20including%20research%20papers%20and%20his%20experience%20reviewing%20other%20research%20and%20judging%20hackathons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20something%20I%20specifically%20did%20for%20the%20O-1%20visa%2C%26quot%3B%20Sharanarthi%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20something%20I%20was%20doing%20previously%20as%20well.%20It%20just%20lined%20up%20really%20nicely%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-memos-sent-big-tech-trump-h-1b-changes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EH-1B%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20become%20so%20popular%20that%20beneficiaries%20are%20decided%20via%20a%20lottery%20system%20once%20a%20year%2C%20there%20is%20no%20cap%20on%20the%20number%20of%20O-1%20visas%20the%20country%20will%20grant%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApplications%20are%20also%20accepted%20for%20the%20O-1%20visa%20on%20a%20rolling%20basis%2C%20and%20applicants%20can%20pay%20an%20expedited%20processing%20fee%20of%20around%20%242%2C800%20to%20receive%20a%20determination%20within%2015%20days%2C%20rather%20than%20waiting%20for%20the%20springtime%20lottery%20for%20an%20H-1B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20O-1%20application%20was%20somewhat%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20the%20H-1B%20before%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-h1b-visa-executive-order-100k-fee-renewal-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0increasing%20the%20application%20fee.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaran%20Vaidya%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20AI%20company%20Composio%20and%20an%20O-1%20visa%20holder%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20O-1%20visa%2C%20which%20was%20granted%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20cost%20less%20than%20%2410%2C000%2C%20including%20legal%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20both%20the%20H-1B%20and%20O-1%20visas%20require%20an%20employer's%20sponsorship%20to%20be%20processed%2C%20the%20O-1%20has%20a%20key%20benefit%20over%20the%20H-1B%2C%20Ullyott%20said%3A%20its%20renewability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20three-year%20visa%20that%20can%20be%20renewed%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%2C%20whereas%20an%20H-1B%20is%20typically%20six%20years%2C%20and%20then%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20permanent%20residency%20underway%2C%26quot%3B%20Ullyott%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20can%20be%20on%20an%20O-1%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20I'm%20on%20my%20fifth%20O-1%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20drawback%2C%20however%2C%20Ullyott%20said.%20In%20addition%20to%20being%20less%20expensive%2C%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20process%20is%20more%20straightforward%20and%20less%20subjective%20than%20the%20O-1%2C%20so%20some%20employers%20are%20hesitant%20to%20take%20the%20chance%20on%20an%20O-1%20application%20if%20there's%20any%20ambiguity%20in%20whether%20the%20candidate%20is%20qualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20prove%20yourself%20extraordinary%2C%20but%20if%20you%20think%20you%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20criteria%20fulfilled%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20an%20amazing%20visa%2C%26quot%3B%20Vaidya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-einstein-o1-visa-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1758471832000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68cf6b5c183847aa39d72f49%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-einstein-o1-visa-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20changes%20to%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20immigration%20specialists%20point%20to%20a%20potential%20s