%20alt%3D%5C%22Close%20up%20photo%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20making%20a%20shushing%20gesture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68cc63e9183847aa39d70f71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20cracking%20down%20on%20free%20expression%2C%20America%20has%20two%20colorful%20and%20distinct%20traditions.%20And%20one%20is%20playing%20out%20in%20business%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20might%20be%20called%20the%20Direct%20Method%3A%20The%20government%20brings%20down%20the%20hammer%20of%20censorship%20by%20criminally%20prosecuting%20an%20individual%20or%20business%20directly%20for%20their%20speech.%20From%20World%20War%20I%20through%20the%201920s%2C%20laws%20like%20the%20Espionage%20Act%20authorized%20imprisoning%20activists%20and%20newspaper%20publishers%20who%20circulated%20anti-war%20ideas.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Sedition%20Act%20of%201798%20effectively%20made%20it%20illegal%20to%20criticize%20the%20sitting%20president%2C%20John%20Adams%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20prosecution%20of%20at%20least%2025%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20tradition%20of%20censorship%20could%20be%20called%20the%20Indirect%20Method%2C%20utilizing%20what%20First%20Amendment%20scholars%20sometimes%20call%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20coercion.%26quot%3B%20In%20this%20approach%2C%20the%20government%20leverages%20all%20the%20creative%20ways%20it%20can%20to%20punish%20speech%20%3Cem%3Eperipherally%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20by%20withholding%20certain%20benefits%2C%20making%20regulatory%20tweaks%2C%20or%20tagging%20groups%20with%20toxic%20legal%20designations%20in%20national%20security%20or%20the%20tax%20code.%20This%20tradition%20came%20to%20define%20the%20McCarthy-era%20crackdown%20on%20Communist%20sympathizers%2C%20which%20reached%20its%20zenith%20in%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjimmy-kimmel-donald-trump-bad-why-explained-free-speech-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuspension%20this%20past%20week%20of%20Jimmy%20Kimmel%20by%20ABC%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20apparent%20behest%20of%20FCC%20Chairman%20Brendan%20Carr%20%E2%80%94%20bears%20the%20features%20of%20soft%20coercion.%20Expressing%20displeasure%20at%20Kimmel's%20characterization%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharlie-kirk-microsoft-nasdaq-delta-office-depot-employees-public-comments-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECharlie%20Kirk's%20assassin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Carr%20appeared%20on%20a%20podcast%20to%20announce%20that%20he%20would%20consider%20regulatory%20punishments%20for%20ABC%20if%20it%20didn't%20remove%20Kimmel%20from%20the%20air%2C%20before%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20either%20do%20this%20the%20easy%20way%2C%20or%20the%20hard%20way.%26quot%3B%20ABC%20announced%20Kimmel's%20suspension%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehours%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20followed%20was%20a%20predictable%20ritual.%20As%20a%20nationwide%20chorus%20of%20political%20and%20business%20icons%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Barack%20Obama%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-key-points-elon-musk-interview-joe-rogan-doge-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJoe%20Rogan%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-former-ceo-michael-eisner-bob-iger-jimmy-kimmel-suspension-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDisney%20CEO%20Michael%20Eisner%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20raised%20their%20voice%20in%20defense%20of%20free%20speech%2C%20MAGA%20partisans%20charged%20Democrats%20with%20bad%20faith%2C%20claiming%20that%20activists%20were%20merely%20being%20served%20their%20own%20medicine%20of%20%26quot%3Bconsequence%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeneath%20MAGA's%20reversal%20is%20a%20point%20worthy%20of%20reflection.%20The%20First%20Amendment%20only%20prohibits%20censorship%20by%20government%2C%20not%20by%20private%20businesses.%20Nevertheless%2C%20corporations%20and%20universities%2C%20no%20less%20than%20government%20bureaucrats%2C%20can%20also%20practice%20soft%20coercion.%20%26quot%3BGovernment%20is%20not%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20can%20make%20you%20unfree%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-pete-buttigieg-bio-age-family-key-positions-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPete%20Buttiegieg%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20when%20running%20for%20president%20%E2%80%94%20so%20can%20%26quot%3Byour%20neighbor%2C%26quot%3B%20your%20%26quot%3Bcable%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20employer.%20It's%20when%20these%20two%20forces%20%3Cem%3Econspire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20result%2C%20historically%2C%20spells%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recruitment%20of%20private%20actors%20for%20government%20ends%20is%20the%20marquee%20feature%20of%20soft%20coercion.%20And%20in%20Carr's%20remarks%2C%20several%20scholars%20have%20identified%20the%20same%20DNA%20signature%20that%20came%20to%20define%20the%20Red%20Scare%20of%20the%201950s.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20clearly%20a%20case%20of%20unconstitutional%20threats%20and%20coercion%20of%20a%20private%20actor%2C%26quot%3B%20Evelyn%20Douek%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20Law%20School%20who%20teaches%20the%20First%20Amendment%2C%20wrote%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BLike%20the%20McCarthy%20Era%2C%20the%20government%20is%20relying%20on%20private%20actors%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20speech%20repression%20on%20its%20behalf.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201950s%2C%20federal%20and%20state%20governments%20found%20creative%20ways%20to%20induce%20private%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20Hollywood%20studios%2C%20unions%2C%20and%20universities%20%E2%80%94%20to%20purge%20or%20blacklist%20unwanted%20speakers.%20Less%20appreciated%2C%20but%20no%20less%20vast%2C%20was%20the%20pressure%20campaign%20waged%20on%20private%20industry.%20As%20historian%20Ellen%20Schrecker%20describes%20in%20her%20book%20%26quot%3BMany%20Are%20the%20Crimes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20country's%20corporate%20behemoths%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20engineering%20%E2%80%94%20GE%2C%20Bethlehem%20Steel%2C%20RCA%2C%20Lockheed%2C%20General%20Motors%2C%20and%20others%20%E2%80%94%20were%20enlisted%20to%20cooperate%20with%20FBI%20and%20Pentagon%20loyalty%20screening%20programs%2C%20effectively%20monitoring%20the%20political%20views%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20executives%20resisted%20somewhat%2C%20such%20as%20those%20at%20Ford%2C%20the%20overwhelmingly%20majority%20complied.%20The%20auto%20giants%2C%20particularly%20dependent%20on%20government%20defense%20contracts%2C%20were%20among%20the%20most%20galvanized%20by%20threats%20of%20investigations%20or%20lost%20business.%20GM%20officials%20repeatedly%20testified%20before%20Congress%2C%20required%20political%20loyalty%20oaths%20from%20unions%2C%20established%20a%20%26quot%3Bloyalty%20and%20security%26quot%3B%20office%2C%20and%20preemptively%20fired%20workers%20flagged%20in%20reports%20by%20HUAC.%20In%201958%2C%20across%20all%20areas%20of%20employment%2C%20estimates%20suggest%20as%20many%20as%20one%20in%20five%20of%20Americans%20were%20subject%20to%20some%20form%20of%20loyalty%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20respects%2C%20the%20second%20Trump%20administration's%20own%20efforts%20mirror%20this%201950s-era%20paradigm%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20Red%20Scare%2C%20but%20a%20Woke%20Scare.%20Under%20the%20auspices%20of%20reigning%20in%20far-left%20ideology%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20implemented%20a%20concerted%20crackdown%20on%20speech%20by%20foreigners%20(should%20they%20write%20an%20impolitic%20op-ed)%2C%20private%20universities%20(should%20they%20fail%20to%20make%20ideological%20adjustments%2C%20like%20firing%20DEI%20staff)%2C%20and%20law%20firms%20(should%20they%20advocate%20insufficiently%20for%20government-approved%20causes).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20broadcasters%2C%20Carr's%20rationale%20may%20be%20rooted%20in%20the%20First%20Amendment%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bgovernment%20speech%26quot%3B%3A%20while%20it%20can't%20interfere%20with%20others'%20speech%2C%20government%20doesn't%20have%20to%20spend%20%3Cem%3Eits%20%3C%2Fem%3Emoney%20on%20speech%20it%20dislikes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20these%20are%20the%20government's%20licenses%2C%20after%20all.%20That%20argument%2C%20too%2C%20echoes%201950s-era%20tactics%20of%20soft%20coercion%3A%20Here%2C%20as%20then%2C%20the%20administration%20hasn't%20made%20it%20criminal%20to%20advocate%20left-wing%20causes%2C%20teach%20left-wing%20ideas%2C%20or%20litigate%20for%20left-wing%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20you%20do%2C%20you%20stand%20to%20lose%20your%20green%20card%2C%20your%20research%20funding%2C%20your%20security%20clearance%2C%20and%20now%2C%20your%20broadcast%20license.%20Corporate%20America%20has%20taken%20heed%20of%20this%20message%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-dei-tariffs-taxes-business-uncertainty-scaredy-cat-capitalism-anxiety-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETarget%20rolling%20back%20its%20DEI%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20Paramount%20paying%20Trump%20a%20%2416%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-paramount-skydance-pay-new-normal-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esettlement%20of%20his%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20editing%20of%20a%20%26quot%3B60%20Minutes%26quot%3B%20interview%20with%20Kamala%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20vast%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20practice%20of%20soft%20coercion%20is%20also%20easily%20comprehensible.%20It%20follows%20three%20basic%20techniques%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Heckler's%20Veto%2C%20jawboning%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20vagueness%20%E2%80%94%20which%20collectively%20nudge%20or%20compel%20Americans%20and%20their%20employers%20to%20suppress%20certain%20types%20of%20speech%20on%20the%20administration's%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20tactic%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BHeckler's%20Veto%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20the%20government%20outsources%20the%20task%20of%20censorship%20to%20crowds%20of%20private%20citizens%2C%20then%20looks%20the%20other%20way%20while%20the%20mob%20wreaks%20havoc.%20This%20past%20week%2C%20while%20guest-hosting%20%26quot%3BThe%20Charlie%20Kirk%20Show%2C%26quot%3B%20Vice%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-charlie-kirk-death-celebration-call-employers-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJD%20Vance%20called%20on%20millions%20of%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20action.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20see%20someone%20celebrating%20Charlie's%20murder%2C%20call%20them%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Vance%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20hell%2C%20call%20their%20employer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20bad%20morals%20to%20celebrate%20someone's%20murder.%20But%20it%20is%20bad%20civics%20for%20a%20head%20of%20state%20to%20enforce%20morals%20by%20punitive%20threat.%20The%20illegality%20of%20such%20a%20scheme%20would%20be%20obvious%20if%20Vance%20had%20made%20this%20request%20not%20of%20private%20citizens%2C%20but%20of%20the%20FBI.%20Vance's%20exhortation%20recalls%20the%20FBI's%20loyalty%20program%20but%20in%20reverse%3A%20a%20national%20snitch%20line%2C%20in%20which%20private%20citizens%20monitor%20their%20bosses.%20As%20Douek%20put%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20use%20its%20power%20to%20force%20private%20actors%20to%20do%20for%20it%20what%20it%20couldn't%20do%20directly%20%E2%80%94%20suppress%20protected%20political%20expression.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20tactic%20is%20%26quot%3Bjawboning.%26quot%3B%20The%20term%20refers%20to%20a%20strategy%20in%20which%20government%20officials%20improperly%20lobby%20a%20private%20actor%20to%20remove%20or%20censor%20third-party%20speech%2C%20often%20using%20vague%20or%20implied%20threats.%20Until%20recently%2C%20it%20was%20Democrats%20who%20had%20been%20tarred%20with%20jawboning.%20In%202024%2C%20a%20federal%20court%20ruled%20the%20Biden%20administration%20had%20inappropriately%20pressured%20Facebook%20and%20Twitter%20to%20combat%20vaccine-related%20and%20other%20misinformation.%20Carr's%20implied%20threat%20to%20ABC%20maps%20with%20laser%20precision%20onto%20the%20same%20jawboning%20offense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20and%20final%20tactic%20of%20soft-coercion%20censorship%20is%20the%20use%20of%20vagueness.%20Instead%20of%20writing%20laws%20that%20articulate%20clearly%20what%20speech%20is%20banned%2C%20a%20purposefully%20vague%20law%20(or%20executive%20order)%20leaves%20doubt%20as%20to%20what%20speech%20is%20legal%20and%20which%20is%20criminal.%20Amid%20this%20confusion%2C%20citizens%20come%20to%20live%20under%20perpetual%20uncertainty%20that%20their%20speech%20%E2%80%94%20the%20next%20text%2C%20tweet%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-slack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESlack%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20might%20or%20might%20not%20invite%20the%20wrath%20of%20criminal%20prosecution.%20Vagueness%20is%20a%20First%20Amendment%20violation%20because%20of%20its%20unusual%20power%20to%20achieve%20widespread%20self-censorship%20not%20by%20fiat%2C%20but%20doubt%20%E2%80%94%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bchilling%26quot%3B%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVagueness%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20administration's%20censorship%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20entirety%20of%20which%20could%20be%20conceived%20as%20one%20massive%2C%20rolling%20vagueness%20violation.%20Consider%20two%20recent%20examples%3A%20A%20%2415%20billion%20lawsuit%20against%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20for%20defamation%20(dismissed%20this%20week%20by%20a%20federal%20judge%20as%20%26quot%3Bimproper%20and%20impermissible%26quot%3B)%2C%20and%20an%20executive%20order%20banning%20flag%20burning%20(a%20black-letter%20First%20Amendment%20violation).%20But%20why%20bring%20lawsuits%20and%20executive%20orders%20that%20can't%20be%20enforced%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20maneuvers%20have%20been%20described%20as%20clear%20attempts%20to%20make%20Trump's%20dissatisfaction%20plainly%20understood.%20In%20reality%2C%20the%20censorship%20campaign%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20seemingly%20intended%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20understood%20%E2%80%94%20designed%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20clearly%20prohibit%20speech%20but%20instead%20invite%20the%20question%20whether%20it%20is.%20Trump%20strikes%20a%20bargain%20with%20law%20firms%2C%20for%20example%2C%20but%20the%20agreements%20aren't%20publicly%20written%20down%2C%20and%20no%20one%20publicly%20knows%20who%20has%20agreed%20to%20what.%20Trump%20bans%20the%20Associated%20Press%20from%20the%20White%20House%20grounds%20for%20using%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BGulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20grants%20access%20to%20other%20outlets%20that%20use%20the%20same%20phrase%2C%20leaving%20lawyers%20to%20speculate%20about%20Trump's%20motives%20in%20court.%20Even%20Carr's%20comments%20this%20past%20week%20resound%20in%20the%20Kafkaesque%2C%20accusing%20ABC%20of%20a%20vague%20failure%20to%20serve%20%26quot%3Bthe%20public%20interest.%26quot%3B%20These%20lawsuits%20and%20executive%20orders%20serve%20a%20similar%20purpose%3A%20to%20signal%20loudly%20that%20it%20doesn't%20credit%20the%20First%20Amendment%20rules%20we%20have%20come%20to%20accept%20as%20ironclad%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20invite%20the%20next%20journalist%2C%20or%20activist%2C%20to%20think%20twice%20about%20which%20free%20speech%20guarantee%20he%20might%20discard%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20the%20McCarthy%20Era%2C%20the%20list%20of%20views%20that%20are%20on%20the%20forbidden%20list%20is%20much%20longer%20and%20more%20amorphous%20and%20growing%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20observes%20Douek.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20just%20about%20suppressing%20Communism%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20it%20seems%20like%20it%20has%20become%20dangerous%20to%20criticize%20the%20government%20or%20its%20allies%20in%20general.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20crucial%3Cspan%3Eremaining%20factor%20that%20explains%20the%20success%20of%20Trump's%20soft%20coercion%3A%20the%20fecklessness%20of%20the%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20law%20firms%2C%20universities%2C%20broadcasters%20%E2%80%94%20that%20have%20capitulated%20to%20it%2C%20sometimes%20with%20remarkable%20speed.%20With%20this%20phenomenon%2C%20we%20are%20reckoning%20with%20the%20casualties%20of%20a%20tragic%20misadventure%20that%20continues%20to%20haunt%20our%20public%20life%3A%20the%20abject%20failure%20of%20mainstream%20Democrats%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20to%20passionately%20defend%20free%20expression%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20first%20principle.%20By%20acquiescing%20to%20progressives%20who%20believed%20otherwise%2C%20the%20liberal%20and%20conservative%20custodians%20of%20these%20institutions%20weakened%20the%20resolve%20of%20their%20leaders%20to%20learn%20the%20vocabulary%20of%20liberal%20resistance.%20Inadvertently%2C%20then%2C%20they%20softened%20the%20institutional%20terrain%20for%20MAGA's%20eventual%20Viktor%20Orban-style%20conquest%20today.%20It%20takes%20years%20to%20become%20proficient%20in%20the%20customs%20of%20capitulation%20%E2%80%94%20to%20become%20acclimated%20to%20incessantly%20kowtowing%20to%20offended%20mobs%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20and%20bending%20to%20political%20whims.%20In%20American%20institutions'%2010-year%20course%20in%20political%20submission%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20the%20left%20was%20their%20first%20teacher.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20people%20begin%20building%20a%20renewed%20case%20for%20free%20speech%2C%20they%20should%20keep%20two%20principles%20in%20mind%2C%20both%20drawn%20from%20the%20lessons%20of%20the%201950s.%20The%20first%20comes%20from%20Arthur%20Koestler.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20help%20people%20being%20right%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Austro-Hungarian%20journalist%20said%20in%201949.%20In%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20left-wing%20activists%20will%20find%20themselves%20making%20points%20about%20free%20expression%20that%20match%20verbatim%20the%20past%20words%20of%20Tucker%20Carlson%20and%20Andrew%20Tate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fact%20they%20must%20be%20prepared%20to%20credit%20and%20embrace.%20Anything%20less%2C%20warned%20Koestler%2C%20will%20poison%20their%20cause%20with%20the%20most%20lethal%20affliction%20any%20argument%20can%20suffer%3A%20%26quot%3BLack%20of%20self-confidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20principle%20comes%20from%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20William%20O.%20Douglas.%20In%201951%2C%20Douglas%20immediately%20identified%20the%20threat%20of%20soft%20coercion%2C%20warning%20that%20America%20would%20soon%20%26quot%3Benter%20dangerous%20territory%20to%20the%20liberties%20of%20every%20citizen.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20articulated%20the%20phenomenon%20that%20explains%20the%20First%20Amendment's%20political%20staying%20power%3A%20the%20confidence%20%E2%80%94%20faith%2C%20really%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20reasoning%20powers%20of%20the%20American%20public%2C%20and%20the%20inherent%20esteem%20it%20conveys%20toward%20one's%20countrymen.%20Famously%2C%20Douglas%20pronounced%20a%20%26quot%3Bconfidence%20in%20the%20ability%20of%20our%20people%20to%20reject%20%5Bthe%5D%20noxious%2C%26quot%3B%20whether%20in%20literature%2C%20theology%2C%20or%20politics.%20Today%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20Americans%20must%20find%20a%20way%20to%20project%20certainty%20in%20the%20reasoning%20capabilities%20of%20every%20American%3A%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20public%20faith.%20This%20will%20remain%20true%20even%20if%20that%20certainty%20is%20later%20proven%20to%20have%20been%20tragically%20misplaced.%20That%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20what%20faith%20requires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbenjamin-wofford%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%2